h1 Panels
.line
h4#basic-panels.Second Basic panels
p.content-bg By default, all the .panel does is apply some basic border and padding to contain some content.
.bs-example
   .panel.panel-default
      .panel-body Basic panel example
.highlight
   pre
      p  < div class="panel panel-default">
      p    < div class="panel-body">
      p      Basic panel example
      p    < /div>
      p  < /div>

h4#panel-heading.Second Panel with heading
p.content-bg Easily add a heading container to your panel with
   span.btn-color .panel-heading
   |  . You may also include any
   |  with a
   span.btn-color .panel-title
   |  class to add a pre-styled heading.
   p.content-bg For proper link coloring, be sure to place links in headings within
   span.btn-color .panel-title.
.bs-example
   .panel.panel-default
      .panel-heading Panel heading without title
      .panel-body Panel content
   .panel.panel-default
      .panel-heading
         .panel-title Panel title
      .panel-body Panel content
.highlight
   pre
      p  < div class="panel panel-default" >
      p     < div class="panel-heading">Panel heading without title </ div >
      p        < div class="panel-body" >
      p           Panel content
      p        < /div>
      p     < /div>
      p  < div class="panel panel-default" >
      p     < div class="panel-title">Panel title </ div >
      p        < div class="panel-body" >
      p           Panel content
      p     < /div>
      p  < /div>

h4#panel-footer.Second Panel with footer
p.content-bg Wrap buttons or secondary text in
   span.btn-color .panel-footer
   |  . Note that panel footers do not inherit colors and borders when using contextual variations as they are not meant to be in the foreground.
.bs-example
   .panel.panel-default
      .panel-body Panel content
      .panel-footer Panel footer
.highlight
   pre
      p  < div class="panel panel-default" >
      p     < div class="panel-body" >
      p        Panel content
      p     < /div>
      p     < div class="panel-footer">Panel footer </ div>
      p  < /div>

