h4#panel-table.Second With tables
p.content-bg Add any non-bordered
   span.btn-color .table
   | within a panel for a seamless design. If there is a
   span.btn-color .panel-body
   | , we add an extra border to the top of the table for separation.
.bs-example
   .panel.panel-default
      .panel-heading Panel heading
      .panel-body
         p Some default panel content here. Nulla vitae elit libero, a pharetra augue. Aenean lacinia bibendum nulla sed consectetur. Aenean eu leo quam. Pellentesque ornare sem lacinia quam venenatis vestibulum. Nullam id dolor id nibh ultricies vehicula ut id elit.
      table.table
         thead
            tr
               th #
               th First Name
               th Last Name
               th Username
         tbody
            tr
               th.row 1
               td Mark
               td Otto
               td @mdo
            tr
               th.row 2
               td Jacob
               td Thornton
               td @fat
            tr
               th.row 3
               td Larry
               td the Bird
               td @twitter
.highlight
   pre
      p  < div class="panel panel-default">
      p     < !-- Default panel contents -->
      p     < div class="panel-heading">Panel heading < /div>
      p     < div class="panel-body" >
      p        < p>...</ p>
      p     < /div>
      p     < !-- Table -->
      p     < table class="table">
      p        ...
      p     < /table >
      p  < /div>
p.content-bg If there is no panel body, the component moves from panel header to table without interruption.
